{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17595228","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17595228"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:01:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:01:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15338"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15338","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15338"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.19,0.13,0.19,0.03,0.45]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8029"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61114"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8029","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8029"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15338"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46560"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"},{"type":"tags","id":"9882"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19506"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19510"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61114","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61114"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe liver plays a crucial role in maintaining vascular tone and haemodynamic stability through various mediators.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the haemodynamic changes in cirrhosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreased circulating vasodilators","Nitric oxide is the primary vasodilatory mediator","Reduced endothelial nitric oxide production","Decreased cardiac output","Increased systemic vascular resistance"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECirrhosis is characterized by profound haemodynamic changes. \u003Cstrong\u003ECirculating vasodilators\u003C/strong\u003E are increased, not decreased. \u003Cstrong\u003ENitric oxide\u003C/strong\u003E is indeed the primary vasodilatory mediator in cirrhosis, produced by endothelial nitric oxide synthase. \u003Cstrong\u003EEndothelial nitric oxide production\u003C/strong\u003E is actually increased, not reduced. \u003Cstrong\u003ECardiac output\u003C/strong\u003E is increased as part of the hyperdynamic circulation. \u003Cstrong\u003ESystemic vascular resistance\u003C/strong\u003E is decreased due to vasodilation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese changes lead to splanchnic vasodilation, portal hypertension, and a hyperdynamic circulatory state. The increased nitric oxide production contributes to the development of portal hypertension and its complications including ascites and hepatorenal syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Cirrhosis leads to increased nitric oxide production via endothelial nitric oxide synthase, causing splanchnic vasodilation","Cirrhosis is characterized by a hyperdynamic circulation with increased cardiac output","Cirrhosis results in increased circulating vasodilators and decreased vascular resistance"],"references":["Joseph A, Samant H. Jaundice. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31334972","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.004. Epub 2019 Oct 31. PMID: 31753251; PMCID: PMC6986808"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46560"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15338"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46560","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/46560"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-15T00:30:08+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-15T00:31:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8029"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61114"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4926"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiovascular","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:14:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T09:50:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"d